<F P=106> [News Report: "Pakistan-Iran Agreement on Eradicating Drug </F>
Smuggling"] 
  [Text] Islamabad, 8 February (TV Report)--Pakistan and Iran 
have expressed agreement to end drug smuggling and have closer 
relations. This agreement was reached after a three-day meeting 
of a special Iran-Pakistan committee in Islamabad. Iran's 
minister of political and social affairs, Ali Reza Tabish, and 
Pakistan's secretary of internal affairs, Jamshed Barki, signed 
this agreement today and during their talks exchanged ideas 
about increasing trade and communication across the border. 

